  Next.js v16.1.1, which subsequently required adapting the Prisma configuration
  and ESLint setup to the new version's breaking changes. Finally, persistent
  Vercel deployment failures were traced to the Prisma client attempting to
  connect during the build phase without a , which was resolved by
  implementing a lazy-loading mechanism for the Prisma client. All issues were
  successfully addressed, and Vercel deployments are now passing.
